&nbsp; <font color="#b336b3"><b>All-purpose mortgage</b>&nbsp;</font>&nbsp;<strong>:</strong>&nbsp;
&nbsp; An all-purpose mortgage loan is a loan given against collateral of an existing property. There are two types of mortgage loans: Mortgage loan for housing purposes All-purpose mortgage loan In both cases the property serves as collateral to the bank for the loan. The difference between the loans is in the cost of money - the interest rate. In mortgage loans for housing the interest rate will be lower. A mortgage loan for housing is a loan given for purchasing an additional property and an all-purpose mortgage loan is a loan given against an existing property for any purpose that is not purchasing an existing property. What is an all-purpose mortgage loan? An all-purpose mortgage loan is essentially a loan given against collateral of an existing property, when the purpose of the loan is not for purchasing a property or expanding the property against building permits. An all-purpose mortgage loan can be for property renovation, closing existing loans and additional obligations, purchasing a car, furniture, etc... An all-purpose loan can be obtained up to 50% of property value. That is, if we own a property worth ₪1,000,000 we can get an all-purpose loan up to ₪500,000 minus the existing mortgage. That is, if we own a property worth ₪1,000,000 with a mortgage of ₪350,000, we can get an all-purpose loan of ₪150,000. That is - up to 50% financing of property value. Just as you need to approve obtaining a mortgage loan, the same applies to an all-purpose loan against property, you need to obtain preliminary approval for the loan. What are the criteria for obtaining an all-purpose mortgage loan: Proper checking account conduct for 3 months Proper conduct in mortgage loan for the last two years if there is an existing mortgage Proper credit history Proper financing percentage Proper repayment ratio - income high enough relative to required loan All-purpose mortgage - when to take and what are the advantages: Consolidating existing loans for long term to reduce monthly payments Easier cash flow Reducing obligation (credit) in bank account Chance for new loan at cheaper interest rate Loan for various purposes in relatively high amounts. Maximum financing utilization against existing property for various purposes such as purchasing additional investment property Attractive interest rates For initial consultation without obligation Specializations New mortgage Price-to-buyer mortgage Self-construction mortgage Reverse mortgage Mortgage refinancing All-purpose mortgage Supplementary mortgage Mortgage for rejected applicants Non-bank mortgage Loan consolidation
